now, let me also answer to yznie's question.
he asked, whether we should analyse both threes same time

double-three is a move that connects two open threes
see if one of the lines is an open three or not
if it is, then you will know it.
you do the same analysis for another three,
or perhaps you have more lines crossing there..
and we can find it out by analysing every three separately
if we will start analysing same time, then it will become a chaos
because it will be impossible to make logical analysis then
i will wonder if this is open four
i go right away, pick another line randomly
is it open four, yes it is
then i same time analyse downwards
then i randomly pick another three
ok i move back some steps
starting from the point we suspect
indeed, here can black play also
but now, see, 5_17_13 is not a three anymore
and if its not three, then all lines are not three
thats why we cannot analyse many lines same time, because it becomes a chaos
like in math, you cannot calculate two answers with one formula at the same time
you can do them one after another
